  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "With the next breaking release solidity will remove the ``constant`` field from the JSON ABI for contract functions, since it is redundant (``constant`` is the same as ``stateMutability === 'view' || stateMutability === 'pure'``).\r\n\r\nI'm in the process of implementing this change in the solidity repo, but we want to make sure that everything that depends on the ``constant`` field can be updated first.\r\n\r\nI think the main change that is required on your end, should be in ``truffle-compile/index.js``. However, I'm not an expert for your code base and any help would be highly appreciated. @gnidan @cgewecke?",
